<% content_for :title, "Cookie Policy - Gleania" %>
<% content_for :description, "How Gleania uses cookies and similar technologies." %>

<section class="relative pt-28 pb-10 overflow-hidden">
  <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-b from-primary-500/5 to-transparent"></div>
  <div class="absolute -top-24 left-1/2 -translate-x-1/2 w-[650px] h-[650px] bg-accent-500/10 rounded-full blur-[140px] pointer-events-none"></div>

  <div class="relative mx-auto max-w-4xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight text-white">Cookie Policy</h1>
    <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-gray-400">Last updated: December 16, 2025</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 pb-16">
  <div class="legal-card">
    <div class="article-prose">
      <p>
        This Cookie Policy explains how Gleania uses cookies and similar technologies when you
        visit our website and use our Service. This policy should be read alongside our
        <%= link_to "Privacy Policy", privacy_path %>.
      </p>

      <h2>What Are Cookies?</h2>
      <p>
        Cookies are small text files stored on your device (computer, tablet, or mobile) when you
        visit a website. They help websites function properly, remember your preferences, and
        understand how you use the site.
      </p>
      <p>Similar technologies include:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Local Storage:</strong> Data stored in your browser that persists until cleared</li>
        <li><strong>Session Storage:</strong> Temporary data cleared when you close your browser</li>
        <li><strong>Pixels/Beacons:</strong> Small images that track page visits (we don't use these)</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Cookies We Use</h2>
      
      <h3>Essential Cookies (Required)</h3>
      <p>
        These cookies are necessary for the Service to function. Without them, you cannot use
        core features like logging in. They cannot be disabled.
      </p>
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Cookie</th>
            <th>Purpose</th>
            <th>Duration</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td><code>_gleania_session</code></td>
            <td>Maintains your login session and stores session data</td>
            <td>Session / 2 weeks</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><code>remember_token</code></td>
            <td>Keeps you logged in if you select "Remember me"</td>
            <td>30 days</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><code>csrf_token</code></td>
            <td>Protects against cross-site request forgery attacks</td>
            <td>Session</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <h3>Preference Cookies (Functional)</h3>
      <p>
        These cookies remember your settings and preferences to enhance your experience.
      </p>
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Cookie</th>
            <th>Purpose</th>
            <th>Duration</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td><code>theme</code></td>
            <td>Remembers your light/dark mode preference</td>
            <td>1 year</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><code>sidebar_collapsed</code></td>
            <td>Remembers sidebar state in the dashboard</td>
            <td>1 year</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <h2>Analytics</h2>
      <p>
        We prioritize your privacy and use <strong>cookieless analytics</strong> to understand
        how the Service is used. This means:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>No tracking cookies are placed on your device</li>
        <li>No cross-site tracking</li>
        <li>No personal data is collected for analytics</li>
        <li>We only collect aggregated, anonymized usage statistics</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        This approach allows us to improve the Service while respecting your privacy and
        complying with privacy regulations without requiring cookie consent banners for analytics.
      </p>

      <h2>Third-Party Cookies</h2>
      <p>
        We minimize third-party cookies. However, some may be set by:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Google OAuth:</strong> If you sign in with Google, Google may set cookies for authentication</li>
        <li><strong>Cloudflare:</strong> Our infrastructure provider may set security cookies to protect against attacks</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        These third-party cookies are subject to the respective providers' privacy policies.
      </p>

      <h2>Managing Cookies</h2>
      <p>
        You can control cookies through your browser settings. Most browsers allow you to:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>View what cookies are stored</li>
        <li>Delete all or specific cookies</li>
        <li>Block all or third-party cookies</li>
        <li>Set preferences for specific websites</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        <strong>Note:</strong> Blocking essential cookies will prevent the Service from functioning
        properly. You won't be able to log in or use authenticated features.
      </p>
      
      <h3>Browser-Specific Instructions</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="https://support.google.com/chrome/answer/95647" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google Chrome</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://support.mozilla.org/en-US/kb/cookies-information-websites-store-on-your-computer" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Mozilla Firefox</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://support.apple.com/guide/safari/manage-cookies-sfri11471/mac" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Apple Safari</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/microsoft-edge/delete-cookies-in-microsoft-edge-63947406-40ac-c3b8-57b9-2a946a29ae09" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Microsoft Edge</a></li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Do Not Track</h2>
      <p>
        Some browsers offer a "Do Not Track" (DNT) setting. Since we use cookieless analytics
        and don't track users across sites, we effectively honor DNT by default.
      </p>

      <h2>Updates to This Policy</h2>
      <p>
        We may update this Cookie Policy from time to time to reflect changes in our practices
        or for legal reasons. We will update the "Last updated" date when changes are made.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact Us</h2>
      <p>
        If you have questions about our use of cookies, please contact us via our
        <%= link_to "contact page", contact_path %>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
